ent-AU14USCMclothingequipmentvendor = USCM apparel vendor
    .desc =
        An automated dispenser rack, hooked up to a small storage of US Colonial Marine Corps apparel. Standard issue aboard naval vessels, military outposts, corporate-science installations and civilian colonies across the frontier. Manufactured to outfit personnel rapidly following cryogenic hypersleep or emergency mobilization.
        For full operational readiness, select one item from each section: fatigues with a webbing, footwear, gloves, headgear, armor, backpack, belt and a pouch.
ent-AU14USCMcorpsmanvendor = USCM corpsman medical vendor
    .desc =
        An automated medical rack, hooked up to a compact stock of US Colonial Marine Corps trauma supplies. Standard issue for corpsmen aboard naval vessels, outposts and colonies where casualties arrive faster than reinforcements. Designed for rapid reconstitution of combat medics following cryogenic hypersleep or emergency call-up.
        Corpsman protocol: select the essential equipment set, storage and limited medications.
ent-AU14USCMaircrewvendor = USASF aircrew vendor
    .desc =
        An automated dispenser rack, hooked up to a small storage of US Aero Space Force aircrew flight and support gear. Engineered to get flight personnel flight-ready in seconds after cryogenic hypersleep or scramble orders.
        Aircrew protocol: select a set of fatigues, the essential medical equipment and storage kit.
ent-AU14USCMcommandequipmentvendor = USCM command vendor
    .desc = An automated command rack, hooked up to a restricted storage of US Colonial Marine Corps command-leadership equipment. Manufactured to equip commanding personnel following cryogenic hypersleep or an emergency directive is issued.
ent-AU14USCMSGequipmentvendor = USCM smartgunner equipment vendor
    .desc = An automated smartgunner rack, hooked up to a small armory of US Colonial Marine Corps heavy-weapon operator systems. Standard issue for designated smart-gun crews on naval vessels and high-threat outposts. Built to bring heavy fire support online rapidly after cryogenic hypersleep or emergency mobilization.
ent-AU14USCMsectionleaderequipmentvendor = USCM section leader vendor
    .desc = An automated equipment rack, hooked up to a compact storage of US Colonial Marine Corps section-leadership equipment. Designed for immediate readiness following cryogenic hypersleep or rapid mobilization orders.
ent-AU14USCMWeaponsVendor = USCM weapons rack
    .desc =
        An automated weapons rack, hooked up to a small armory of US Colonial Marine Corps weaponry. Standard issue across the frontier where threats can appear without warning. Engineered to arm personnel in seconds following cryogenic hypersleep or emergency mobilization.
        For immediate combat readiness: select a primary weapon kit and a sidearm.
ent-AU14USCMSpecialWeaponsVendor = USCM special weapons rack
    .desc =
        An automated special weapons rack, hooked up to a restricted armory of US Colonial Marine Corps heavy and breaching ordnance. Standard issue only for qualified operators. Engineered to deliver overwhelming firepower the instant cryogenic hypersleep ends or an emergency mobilization is called.
        Special weapons protocol: one weapon system of choice with a full ammunition loadout and explosives.
ent-AU14USCMequipmentvendor = equipment vendor
    .desc =
        An automated dispenser rack, hooked up to a small storage of US Colonial Marine Corps equipment. Stocked with medical supplies and field gear for rapid deployment following cryogenic hypersleep or emergency mobilization. The interface is intentionally simple, even someone with tunnel-vision and frostbite can operate it.
        Rapid-issue protocol: prioritize medical supplies, a ration pack, an e-tool and sandbags.
